Dr. B. N. Jagtap is the head of the atomic and molecular division at the Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC) in India and a professor at the Indian Institute of Technology Bombay and the Homi Bhabha National Institute, Mumbai . He is also the editor of a quarterly magazine, Indian Nuclear Society News.Cited as the "game changer" in a recent article in Livemint and The Wall Street Journal, his research includes a wide variety of interesting topics such as molecules of importance in astrophysics, atmospheric sciences, pre-biotic molecules (molecules that were formed before the molecules responsible for life on Earth) and ultra-cold atoms (atoms that are cooled close to temperatures near absolute zero).

